From e5d1a01cbc7c42d4c818535346568cba1b8d99d3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sridharan S N <quic_sridsn@quicinc.com>
Date: Wed, 5 Feb 2025 10:02:43 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] usb: misc: qcom_eud: Update the chip enabled as false when
 EUD is disabled.

Update the chip->enabled bool as false when it is disabled.
So the sysfs will reflect the eud state properly.

Change-Id: I91a4b9ec7060e6d2b81402d4a603ff16175445f5
Signed-off-by: Sridharan S N <quic_sridsn@quicinc.com>
---
 drivers/usb/misc/qcom_eud.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/misc/qcom_eud.c b/drivers/usb/misc/qcom_eud.c
index d867a8de9873..e8ab91da23b9 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/misc/qcom_eud.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/misc/qcom_eud.c
@@ -92,6 +92,7 @@ static ssize_t enable_store(struct device *dev,
 			disable_eud(chip);
 	} else {
 		disable_eud(chip);
+		chip->enabled = enable;
 	}
 
 	return count;
-- 
2.34.1

